{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"503b6523-f21b-44dc-8a8c-a06dd86a0251","content":"Here's the workflow at `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. It triggers on version tags (`v*`), packs your library, and pushes to NuGet using OIDC — no API key needed.\n\n---\n\n**You also need to configure NuGet.org (one-time manual step):**\n\n1. Go to [nuget.org/account/trusted-publishers](https://www.nuget.org/account/trusted-publishers)\n2. Click **Add Trusted Publisher** and fill in:\n   - **Repository owner:** `myorg`\n   - **Repository name:** `mylib`\n   - **Workflow:** `publish.yml`\n   - **Environment:** *(leave blank unless you add a GitHub environment)*\n\n---\n\n**To publish a release:**\n\n```bash\ngit tag v1.0.0\ngit push origin v1.0.0\n```\n\nThe workflow will authenticate via OIDC automatically — the `id-token: write` permission is the key piece that enables the token exchange with NuGet.org. No secrets to manage or rotate.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"df6edb95-c247-44be-ac1b-744469fdb20d","outputTokens":243,"requestId":"1024:CA1D0:2A31AFF:2E7A70A:69FD344D"},"id":"72730d9e-5d27-4ce7-b059-98185135afa2","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:54:46.518Z","parentId":"de72c1b0-25e4-4610-8fa6-508a93ad18d4"}
